rComments: He's a good and nice professor who teaches efficiently. He's kind and helps in any way he can. However he assigns essays less than a week before it's due. So you'll have to cram your time to get the work in on time. He's not a tough grader so you'll be okay. You're going to have to manage your time well to keep up with the classes.

rComments: One of the best profs I've ever had! His lectures are very organized and inspirational. He is kind and cares for students. Not a hard marker. Wish there are more profs like him.

Professor Valpy is a boon to the Book and Media Studies program. He is the type of lecturer that aims to instill insights and experiences to his students:  he gives a theoretical crash course to newspaper theory while supplementing it with lectures given by prominent guest speakers (i.e. Robyn Doolittle). You will be enlightened in every class.
